        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 7:02PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 701 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking numerous gusty
thunderstorms across northeastern Illinois. All were moving
northeast at 20 to 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Oakwood Hills, Rolling Meadows, Valley View, Lily Lake, Hawthorn
Woods, Ridgefield, Highwood, Round Lake Beach, Hainesville, South
Elgin, Huntley, South Barrington, Gurnee, Gilberts, Buffalo Grove,
Wayne, Waukegan, Volo, Crystal Lake, Long Lake, Barrington Hills,
Lake Catherine, Palatine, Hoffman Estates, and Forest Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
